.:: Puzzle 2x5-Level-1-13::.
City: edinburgh, hamburg, new-york, miami, nizza
The people use 5 different means of transport: bus, snowmobile, subway, train, tram
1. the person traveling to hamburg is on the right of the person driving the bus##1
2. the person driving the subway is on the far right##1
3. the person driving the snowmobile is the person traveling to edinburgh##1
4. the person traveling to nizza is the person driving the subway##1
5. the person driving the train is on the left of the person traveling to edinburgh##1
6. the person traveling to miami is in the middle##1
7. the person traveling to miami is on the right of the person traveling to edinburgh##1

.:: Answer ::.
|               |   1    |     2      |    3    |    4     |    5    |
| City   | new-york | edinburgh      | miami | hamburg | nizza |
| Transport     | train  | snowmobile | bus     | tram     | subway  |

